A Federal High Court sitting in Abuja has acquitted and discharged Jide Omokore, chairman of Atlantic Energy Drilling Concepts Nigeria Limited, of $1.6bn fraud allegations. Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) arraigned Omokore alongside Victor Briggs, Abiye Membere, and David Mbanefo on a 15-count charge on July 4, 2016. They were accused of fraudulently diverting about $1.6bn alleged to be part of proceeds of sales of petroleum products belonging to the federal government. More laterâ€¦ 